                            Situated in the Mughal capital of Shahjahanabad (today Old Delhi), it served as the imperial mosque of the
                            Mughal emperors until the demise of the empire in 1857. The Jama Masjid was regarded as a symbolic gesture of
                            Islamic power across India, well into the colonial era.
                        </p>
